Traffic management is an important aspect of smart cities. Traditional traffic systems use fixed timers, which are not efficient during varying traffic conditions.

This project introduces a smarter approach using queues:

Each lane is treated as a queue.
Vehicles enter at the rear and exit from the front.
The system dynamically decides which lane gets the green signal.

Key features:

Fair vehicle movement using FIFO principle
Priority handling for ambulances
Dynamic lane selection based on traffic density

This approach reduces waiting time and improves emergency response.
